## Riverpod State Management

| Use Case | Provider Type |
|----------|--------------|
| Data fetch | `FutureProvider` / `.family` |
| Realtime | `StreamProvider` |
| Mutations | `StateNotifierProvider` |
| Simple state | `StateProvider` |
| Derived | `Provider` |

- `ConsumerWidget` / `ConsumerStatefulWidget` for Riverpod widgets
- `ref.watch()` in build, `ref.read()` for actions, `ref.listen()` for side effects
- `AsyncValue.guard()` for error handling
- `ref.invalidate()` after mutations
- Co-locate providers with features
- Dispose channels in `StateNotifier.dispose()`

---

## Security

- NEVER commit `.env` files or hardcode secrets
- `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` = client-safe; `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` = server-only
- Verify `auth.currentUser` before protected operations
- Edge Functions: verify JWT via `auth.getUser()`, return 401 if invalid
- RLS enabled on every table; never `WITH CHECK (TRUE)` without justification
- Validate file types/sizes before upload
- Serve uploads via CDN only

---

## Git Workflow

- Branches: `feature/`, `fix/`, `chore/`, `docs/`, `refactor/` + description
- Commits: conventional format ‚Äî `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, `style:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `l10n:`
- Never commit: `.env`, `*.g.dart`, `app_localizations*.dart`, `build/`, `node_modules/`, signing keys
- PR: conventional title + summary + test plan + screenshots (LTR+RTL)
- Never force-push to `main`

